    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-06-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="413" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d413">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Señor Benitez</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Washburn</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry of State for Foreign
                                            affairs,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Luque,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-06-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 20, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Portuguese subject, Don José Maria Leite Pereira, having
                                disappeared some days since from his ordinary residence in Trinidad,
                                in contravention of orders in force, I have the honor to inquire of
                                your excellency if it be true, as the police has been informed, that
                                the said individual is now in the American legation, and for how
                                long since; hoping your excellency will also please inform me of the
                                nature and motive of his remaining in that legation.</p>
                <p>At the same time I beg your excellency will remit me a list of all
                                the persons who, without belonging to the legation, are sheltered in
                                it.</p>
                <p>On this occasion I have the honor to renew to your excellency the
                                assurances of my most distinguished consideration and esteem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GUMESINDO BENITEZ.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles A. Washburn</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister Resident of the United States of
                                        America.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
